ption of those with disabilities are hopefully changing for the better (notably Galligan's Breaking Bad which wonderfully included RJ Mitte and NEVER spotlighted his cerebral palsy, as it should be).<br /><br />It is, however, my hope that one day such an award is not needed, then that will show how far we've come as human beings.","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"3 years ago","ctime":"October 26 2013, 13:23:35 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"Congrats! A very worthy and braggable award! :-)","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://ser-gabriel.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"ser_gabriel","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"ser_gabriel","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://ser-gabriel.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"ser_gabriel","ctime_ts":1382793815,"tracked":0}]}